'''NetRegs''' is a website set up to help small businesses in [[Scotland]] and [[ Northern Ireland]] become more environmentally aware.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/spl/aberdeen/smaller-firms-still-ignorant-of-dirty-practices-1.41430 |first=Rob |last=Edwards |title=Smaller firms still ignorant of dirty practices |work=[[Sunday Herald]] |date=2 October 2005 |accessdate=6 January 2015}}</ref> It has been developed by a partnership between the [[Scottish Environment Protection Agency]] (SEPA) in Scotland and the [[Northern Ireland Environment Agency]] (NIEA) in Northern Ireland.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sepa.org.uk/customer_information/netregs.aspx |title=NetRegs| publisher=Scottish Environment Protection Agency (SEPA) |accessdate=10 July 2013}}</ref> NetRegs is a source of free environmental guidance for small and medium-sized enterprises based in Scotland and Northern Ireland. The website provides information and guidance on key environmental legislation as well as good practice for every type of business. It is free to use and available 24 hours a day. Since 2006 it has also offered to provide updates by email. '''NetRegs''' also provides free e-learning tools, an environmental self assessment tool and hosts the GPPs (Guidance for Pollution Prevention documents, a replacement for the old PPGs) <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fwi.co.uk/news/farmers-offered-help-to-keep-up-with-environmental-regulations.htm |title=Farmers offered help to keep up with environmental regulations |work=[[Farmers Weekly]] |date=25 January 2006 |accessdate=6 January 2015}}</ref>

